"Yes, he does," he answered. When Peter entered the house, Jesus spoke first. "What do you think, Simon?" he asked. "Do the kings of the earth collect taxes and duties? Do they collect them from their own children or from others?"
"From others," Peter answered. "Then the children should not have to pay," Jesus told him.
